  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed rear dormer extension would be an inappropriate addition to a largely unaltered residential row. The alteration to the original roof form would harm the appearance of the Grade II Listed Building, and would be detrimental to the character and appearance of the wider Barnsbury Conservation Area. The development is contrary to Policies D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), D22 (New Development) and D24 (Materials) of Islington Council's Unitary Development Plan (2002), Policy CS9 of the Core Strategy (2011), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002), Islington's Urban Design Guide (2006), and Planning Policy Statement 5: Planning for the Historic Environment."
